<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="561" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,546,1615]" pageId="6" pageNumber="561">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1230,1255]" pageId="6" pageNumber="561">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific epithet refers to the light whitish gray band of pubescence forming a “V” on the pronotum, which resembles a piece of cloth, triangular in shape, worn around the neck, called a “ 
<taxonomicName box="[1238,1339,1266,1291]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Aereniphaula" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="561" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bandana">bandana</taxonomicName>
”.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
